 :tx/rationale "Set t-065fdbaa title=ATT-2-IMPL: Hebbian feedback from verbose-request detection. When an agent requests --verbose or clicks on an omitted section, that's an explicit interest signal. The Hebbian rule: connections that fire together wire together. APPROACH: (1) In status.rs, detect --verbose flag. When present, identify which sections were previously omitted (compare Navigate vs Verbose budget levels). (2) For each newly-revealed section, look up its block label and increment :attention/hebbian-boost by co_activation_weight (default 1.0 for explicit request, 0.5 for same-session, 0.25 for adjacent-session). (3) The hebbian_boost feeds into AcquisitionScore via the impact factor: impact = base_impact + hebbian_boost.clamp(0, 0.5). This means frequently-requested sections auto-promote in future renders. (4) Decay: hebbian_boost *= 0.9 per session (temporal decay prevents permanent promotion). ACCEPTANCE: (A) After --verbose, the expanded sections' hebbian-boost increases. (B) Next bare status call: previously-expanded sections rank higher. (C) After 10 sessions without --verbose, hebbian_boost decays below 0.1. (D) hebbian_boost is clamped to [0, 1.0] to prevent runaway. DEPENDS-ON: ACP-SCORE-1 (all blocks must have scores for boost to matter). TRACES: ADR-FOUNDATION-024, ADR-FOUNDATION-029. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/context.rs"
